Consider the following example in JSX:

```js
const greeting = (
 <div className='greeting'>
 <h2>Hello world!</h2>
 </div>
);
```

If we want to output the same HTML, what goes into `1`, `2`, and `3` when calling `createElement()`?

```js
const greeting = React.createElement(
 __1__,
 { className: 'greeting' },
 React.createElement(
 __2__,
 {},
 __3__
 )
);
```
